---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/js-programming/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Activity 1.2 Arithmetic</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-4" />

        <h2>Introduction</h2>

        <Presentation>
          <section>
            <h3>Activity 1.2</h3>
            <h4 class="text-skynest-theme">Arithmetic</h4>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>Topics</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Arithmetic in programming</li>
              <li>The Number data type</li>
              <li>Math operators</li>
              <li>Operator precedence</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
          <section>
            <p>
              Any useful program, from video games to online stores, relies on
              numbers.
            </p>
            <p>
              Whether it's calculating scores, processing transactions, or
              generating graphics, math is everywhere in software.
            </p>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>
              The <span class="text-skynest-theme">Number</span> Data Type
            </h4>
            <p>
              In JavaScript, the number type represents both integers and
              floating-point (decimal) values.
            </p>
            <AstroCode
              code={"2.5"}
              lang="javascript"
              theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
              inline
            />&nbsp;
            <AstroCode
              code={"401"}
              lang="javascript"
              theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
              inline
            />&nbsp;
            <AstroCode
              code={"-65"}
              lang="javascript"
              theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
              inline
            />&nbsp;
            <AstroCode
              code={"-123.45"}
              lang="javascript"
              theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
              inline
            />&nbsp;
            <AstroCode
              code={"1_000_000"}
              lang="javascript"
              theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
              inline
            />&nbsp;
            <i class="text-skynest-red si-x"></i><AstroCode
              code={'"35"'}
              lang="javascript"
              theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
              inline
            />
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>
              <span class="text-skynest-theme">Demo</span> Print Some Numbers
            </h4>
            <p>
              Use the <AstroCode
                code="console.log()"
                lang={"javascript"}
                inline
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
              /> function to display some numbers on the screen.
            </p>
            <Code
              code={Figure1}
              frame="code"
              lang="javascript"
              title="app.js"
              class="text-start"
            />
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>Math Operators</h4>
            <dl>
              <dd>
                <AstroCode
                  code="+"
                  lang={"javascript"}
                  inline
                  theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                /> Addition
              </dd>
              <dd>
                <AstroCode
                  code="-"
                  lang={"javascript"}
                  inline
                  theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                /> Subtraction
              </dd>
              <dd>
                <AstroCode
                  code="*"
                  lang={"javascript"}
                  inline
                  theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                /> Multiplication
              </dd>
              <dd>
                <AstroCode
                  code="/"
                  lang={"javascript"}
                  inline
                  theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                /> Division: Divides two numbers and returns the quotient as a decimal.
              </dd>
              <dd>
                <AstroCode
                  code="%"
                  lang={"javascript"}
                  inline
                  theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                /> Modulus (Mod): Divides two numbers and returns the <b
                  >remainder</b
                >.
              </dd>
            </dl>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>Order of Operations</h4>
            <p>Use parenthesis for operator precedence.</p>
            <p>
              <AstroCode
                code="3 * 4 + 5"
                lang="javascript"
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              />
            </p>
            <p>
              <AstroCode
                code="3 * (4 + 5)"
                lang="javascript"
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
                inline
              />
            </p>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>Demo: Print Some Math Expressions</h4>
            <p>
              Use <AstroCode
                code="console.log()"
                lang={"javascript"}
                inline
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
              /> to display the result of some math expressions.
            </p>
            <Code
              code={Figure2}
              frame="code"
              lang="javascript"
              title="app.js"
              class="text-start"
            />
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>Key Terms</h4>

            <dl>
              <dt>Data Type</dt>
              <dd>
                A classification for different kinds of information. It tells
                you what kind of data is being stored or used.
              </dd>
              <dt>Integer</dt>
              <dd>
                A data type that stores whole numbers, like 5, 25, or -100.
              </dd>
              <dt>Floating-Point Number</dt>
              <dd>
                A data type that stores numbers with decimal points, like 3.14
                or -99.99.
              </dd>
            </dl>
          </section>
        </Presentation>

        <section id="objectives">
          <h3>Objectives</h3>
          <ul>
            <ListItem variant="1">Write Math Expressions</ListItem>
            <ListItem variant="1"
              >Output numeric values with <AstroCode
                code="console.log()"
                lang={"javascript"}
                inline
                theme={"material-theme-ocean"}
              /></ListItem
            >
            <ListItem variant="1">Document code with comments</ListItem>
            <ListItem variant="1">Practice order of operations</ListItem>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-4" />

        <section id="activity-tasks">
          <h2>Activity Tasks</h2>
          <ul>
            <ListItem variant="2">
              Create a new project named <span class="text-skynest-theme"
                >1-2-arithmetic.js</span
              >.
            </ListItem>
            <ListItem variant="2"> Complete each task individually. </ListItem>
          </ul>

          <h3>
            <span class="text-skynest-theme">Task 1</span>: Addition and
            Subtraction
          </h3>
          <ul>
            <ListItem variant="2">
              Display the result of the addition and subtraction expressions
              using console.log().
            </ListItem>
          </ul>
          <Code
            code={Task1}
            frame="code"
            lang="javascript"
            mark={{ label: "Stop and run your code", range: "14" }}
            showLineNumbers
            title="1-2-arithmetic.js"
          />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>
            <span class="text-skynest-theme">Task 2</span>: Multiplication and
            Division
          </h3>
          <ul>
            <ListItem variant="2">
              Display the result of the multiplication and division expressions
              using console.log().
            </ListItem>
          </ul>
          <Code
            code={Task2}
            frame="code"
            ins={{ range: "14-27" }}
            lang="javascript"
            mark={{ label: "Stop and run your code", range: "28" }}
            showLineNumbers
            title="1-2-arithmetic.js"
          />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>
            <span class="text-skynest-theme">Task 3</span>: Modulo Operation
          </h3>
          <ul>
            <ListItem variant="2">
              Use the mod operator to find the remainder portion of the division
              operation.</ListItem
            >
          </ul>
          <Code
            code={Task3}
            frame="code"
            ins={{ range: "28-32" }}
            lang="javascript"
            mark={{ label: "Stop and run your code", range: "33" }}
            showLineNumbers
            title="1-2-arithmetic.js"
          />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>
            <span class="text-skynest-theme">Task 4</span>: Order of Operations
          </h3>
          <ul>
            <ListItem variant="2">
              Use parenthesis to control the order in which the operations are
              calculated.</ListItem
            >
          </ul>
          <Code
            code={Task4}
            frame="code"
            ins={{ range: "33-38" }}
            lang="javascript"
            mark={{ label: "Stop and run your code", range: "39" }}
            showLineNumbers
            title="1-2-arithmetic.js"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-4" />

        <section id="sample-output">
          <h2>Sample Output</h2>

          <p>
            Your program output should something similar to the sample output
            below.
          </p>

          <Code
            code={SampleOutput}
            frame="terminal"
            lang="txt"
            showLineNumbers={false}
            title="Sample Output"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-4" />

        <section id="reflection">
          <h2>Reflection Questions</h2>

          <p>
            You may write your reflection answers as comments at the bottom of
            your code.
          </p>

          <ol>
            <li>
              How did the use of parentheses change the result in the order of
              operations example? Why is that important when writing code?
            </li>
            <li>
              Which math operator did you find most surprising or unfamiliar in
              JavaScript, and why?
            </li>
            <li>
              Why is it helpful to include spaces around math operators (like +,
              -, *, /) when writing code, even though JavaScript works without
              them?
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-4" />

        <section id="submission">
          <h2>Submission</h2>

          <p>
            Submit your activity and reflection answers to the appropriate
            dropbox.
          </p>
        </section>

        <h1 class="text-center mt-5 text-skynest-theme border border-primary">
          Activity Complete
        </h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
